description:
Operation Julie

Sociopolitical Documentary hosted by Lyn Ebenezer, published by S4C in 1999 - Welsh narration


Information
------------------------------

Lyn Ebenezer presents this drama-documentary about the major Police operation during the 1970s which closed down one of the largest LSD manufacturing rings in the world. Code-named 'Operation Julie', this was one of the largest and most astonishing drugs operation ever, with the focus on secret laboratories in rural mid Wales which produced hundreds of millions of pound worth of LSD. 800 police officers were involved, over 120 people were arrested and LSD tablets with a street value of Ã‚Â£100 million were found.

